            "advisory": "Affected versions of the `starlette` package are vulnerable to Denial of Service (DoS) due to improper handling of large file uploads in multi-part form parsing. The vulnerability exists in the `UploadFile` class, where the logic fails to adequately check if additional bytes will trigger a file rollover, leading to blocking of the main thread. An attacker can exploit this by uploading large files that exceed the default max spool size, causing the event thread to block and preventing the application from accepting new connections.",
